<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->

<!-- PJG 0011 horztab -->
This subpart establishes the basic Agency policies for planning and performing site development work. It also provides
the procedures and guidelines for preparing site development plans consistent with Federal laws, regulations and
Executive Orders. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;1924.102 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
General policy. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(a) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Rural development. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
This subpart provides for the development of building sites and related facilities in rural areas. It is designed
to: 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1) Recognize community needs and desires, and encourage leadership responsibility in local planning, control
and development. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) Recognize standards for building-site design which encourage and lead to the development of economically stable
communities, and the creation of attractive, healthy, and permanent living environments. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) Encourage improvements planned for the site to be the most cost-effective of the practicable alternatives. Encourage
utilities and services utilized to be reliable, efficient and available at reasonable costs. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(4) Provide for a planning process that will consider impacts on the environment and existing development in order
to formulate actions that protect, enhance, and restore environmental quality. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(b) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Subdivisions. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
The Agency does not review or approve subdivisions. Each site approved by the Agency must meet the requirements of
&sect;1924.115 of this subpart, on a site by site basis. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(c) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Development related costs. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1) Applicant.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 The applicant is responsible for all costs incurred before loan and/or grant closing associated with planning, technical
services, and actual construction. These costs may be included in the loan/grant as authorized by Agency regulations.

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2)
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
 Developer.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 The developer is responsible for payment of all costs associated with development under this subpart. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;1924.103 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Scope. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->

<!-- PJG 0011 horztab -->
This subpart is for Agency personnel when considering a site or site development work for Rural Housing (RH) loans
for individuals. It provides supplemental requirements for Rural Rental Housing (RRH) loans, Rural Cooperative
Housing (RCH) loans, Farm Labor Housing (LH) loans and grants, and Rural Housing Site (RHS) loans. It also provides
a site development standard (Exhibit B of this subpart) which supplements this subpart to determine the acceptability
of development. All of this subpart applies to Single Family Housing unless otherwise noted. All of this subpart also
applies to Multiple Family Housing except &sect;&sect;1924.115, 1924.120 and 1924.121, which applies only to Single
Family Housing, and any paragraph specifically shown for Single Family Housing. In addition, the Agency will consult
with appropriate Federal, State, and local agencies, other organizations, and individuals to implement the provisions
of this subpart. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
